<TITLE> Mozambique issues oil exploration tender </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Maputo, Dec 6 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Mozambique on Thursday issued an oil exploration tender for the southern Inhambane province. "We are today announcing the third round of all prospection in Mozambique. We are offering 61,000 square metres divided in nine groups, offshore and onshore, in the districts of Pande and Temane in the southern province of Inhambane," said Carlos Zacarias, a board member of the Mozambique National Petroleum Institute. "We are inviting small and medium companies to participate, but they must show a technical capacity and a strong financial robustness. A minimum of $7 million will be on the table...
